<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-18T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-18T19:00:00-05:00" n="386" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5–1449: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Clark</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                                Canton</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-18T20:00:00-04:00">May 18,
                                    1949—8 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>TelCan 196. ReCantel 378, May 14. Dept considerably interested in
                            organization described reftel and wld appreciate receiving further
                            details with names individuals concerned and continuing reports their
                            progress. Dept now looking into possibility action along lines you
                            suggest and will inform you when thinking more advanced.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>